tail, and he enlightens readers on how to think about the theory physically. Along the way, he dismantles some popular myths and clarifies the novel ways in which quantum field theory is both a theory about fields and about particles. His goal is to raise questions about the philosophical implications of the theory and to offer some tentative interpretive views of his own. This provocative and thoughtful book challenges philosophers to extend their thinking beyond the realm of quantum mechanics and it challenges physicists to consider the philosophical issues that their explorations have encouraged.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aQuantum field theory. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Quantum Theory.2bisacsh  aFock space.  aHeisenberg picture.  aasymptotic freedom.  abare particulars.  acoherent states.  aconfinement.  adeterminables.  adispositions.  afield configuration.  ageneral solutions.  aheuristic substitutions.  aimpact parameters.  ainterpretations.  aloop diagrams.  amass shell.  anegative energy solutions.  anumber operators.  aontology of quantum theories.  apath ntegrals.  apropensities.  aquanta.  aradiative corrections.  arealism.  atheories.  avacuum fluctuations.  awave function renormalization.  azero point energy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691216294zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691216294423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691216294.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEB